    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are golden, push them into 2 <span class=\"text-purple\">[3]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> piles on the baking tray[s]</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>tomato sauce</strong>, then top with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>dried oregano</strong>, <strong>torn mozzarella</strong>, <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>pepperoni slices</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 6-8 min or until the cheese has melted and the pepperoni is crispy</p><p>Once done, set aside for a few min to cool slightly – these are your <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>pepperoni pizza loaded fries</strong></p>",
